# 🧭 PART 1: HOW LOCALPRO BECOMES A BIR-RECOGNIZED POS PROVIDER

You will formalize your position with the Bureau of Internal Revenue as a **POS/CAS solution provider**.


## 🔹 Step-by-Step Process

### 1. Upgrade Business Capability (if needed)

Ensure your business scope includes:

- Software development ✔ (you already have this)
- POS / IT solutions ✔ (add if not stated)

👉 If missing: file **BIR Form 1905 (Update Registration)**

***


### 2. Prepare Accreditation Documents

You don’t “apply like a license”—you **submit system compliance documentation**.


#### Core Documents:

- 📄 System Overview (architecture, modules)
- 📄 Process Flow (sales → receipt → reporting)
- 📄 Sample Official Receipt (very important)
- 📄 VAT Computation Logic
- 📄 Audit Trail Documentation
- 📄 Data Security & Backup Plan

***


### 3. Design POS to Meet BIR Standards

Your system must technically support:

- Unique receipt serial per client
- Non-editable transactions
- Voiding with logs (not deletion)
- Audit trail (user + timestamp)
- Daily sales report (Z-reading equivalent)
- Exportable reports (CSV/PDF)

***


### 4. Optional but Recommended: CAS Registration

If you want **higher credibility + enterprise clients**:

- Register LocalPro POS as a **Computerized Accounting System (CAS)**
- This strengthens your position when pitching hotels, schools, etc.

***


# 🧩 PART 2: CLIENT ONBOARDING FLOW (VERY IMPORTANT)

This is where most POS businesses fail. You will win here.


## 🔄 Standard Client Flow

### STEP 1 — Sales Close

Client agrees to use LocalPro POS

***


### STEP 2 — Collect Client BIR Info

You need:

- TIN
- Business Name
- Registered Address
- VAT / Non-VAT status

***


### STEP 3 — Configure POS

You set:

- Receipt format (with BIR-required fields)
- Serial number range
- Tax settings

***


### STEP 4 — PTU Application (CRITICAL)

👉 Client must apply for:\
**Permit to Use (PTU)**


### You provide:

- POS system documentation
- Sample receipts
- System description

👉 You can upsell:

> “We handle your BIR PTU processing”

***


### STEP 5 — Go Live

Only after PTU approval:

- Activate POS
- Start issuing official receipts

***


